<subSubSection id="32C10D572C4854D298406646A11B2A89" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" type="type">
<paragraph id="E171C05AB1F5AB373F1B42ADDC3EE7C1" pageId="162" pageNumber="163">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03F84CF8C3700F8D11D79B3C7EEF6357" pageId="162" pageNumber="163">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="EC7D688ED8AA7494349771054EFFCC9B" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruprechtii" order="Solanales" pageId="162" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruprechtii">
<emphasis id="71760F9AEE4DF7B4DA9293D285FFEEB4" italics="true" pageId="162" pageNumber="163">Convolvulus ruprechtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Boiss.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D557F387EE45302F036A8501929D7751" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="EFDCDED672279BB6DB7ED36E19D4B4FB" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<pageBreakToken id="EAAD7B310FA6237672D5E6696834AF7F" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" start="start">Distinguishing</pageBreakToken>
features.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA9DB943656DD0D4C1338904889B1D41" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
Leaves and stem silvery with appressed sericeous hairs; spreading hairs absent or almost so. Leaves broadly oblong to obovate, up to three times as long as broad. 
<bibRefCitation id="B2E10DB02F7D5F78DCACACFCE149330E" author="Petrov, VA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="132 - 150" refId="B265" refString="Petrov, VA, 1935. Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium. Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique 44: 132 - 150" title="Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium." volume="44" year="1935">Petrov 1935</bibRefCitation>
: 144 (plate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9A2293A2ABA0A43D3E9ACA34270DA8A" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="34CE45EE7E9F0F80632DB1F8E545DDBE" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA31EE732E66415D1C202E986EFC5478" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
Crimea (
<emphasis id="B9EBFBB23924C10AC8B75B6A5551BD77" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Vasak</emphasis>
s.n. [29/7/1977]); Russia: Dagestan (
<emphasis id="AED00473BE98B41FC9D3EA375482B296" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Tsvelev et al</emphasis>
. 1020, 2850, 3164, 
<emphasis id="1C50A1ABB4AE5D19F2526E9300CC1486" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Alexeenko</emphasis>
952, 9355, 
<emphasis id="B5E6B99077FF810CE7C586CDDFECDFB3" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Grossheim</emphasis>
s.n. [25/6/1915]); Armenia (
<emphasis id="D8377AB2C7CC6DE861FC78B8E1219968" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Fayvush et al.</emphasis>
04-0424); Azerbaijan (
<emphasis id="605FCFAC8C2E45E4BB12C9947CB4695B" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Grossheim et al.</emphasis>
s.n. [10/6/1947]); Iran (
<emphasis id="CA09DB381B8D6DEE21BF536A3E088126" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Miller et al.</emphasis>
s.n. [17/5/2005]). Principally in the eastern Caucasus around 1500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F15E7B9F92951E3568057D91FDB2685F" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C1E8EBED382A1D32D88889429B23214D" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4FE85855D5289EB9B52C566997D1DF75" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName id="D399A2A749A1AA8B05B9732B2FA53CE8" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient., ser. 2, 3: 124. 1856. (Boissier" authorityYear="1856" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus calvertii" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calvertii">
<emphasis id="55C6A29E5DDE19FB01BCA01190063674" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus calvertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the near sessile flowers with bracts often overtopping the heads are distinctive. It is easily confused with 
<taxonomicName id="7D29E8FF523B9472B603E623B6CB25B8" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 81. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus commutatus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="commutatus">
<emphasis id="B040132CCF675FA20868DB2CC403848E" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus commutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6F5D019522A0B561729D5A2E3B823F2B" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 82. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus schirazianus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schirazianus">
<emphasis id="6E0F887E1E5728C759D4AE18C4D3B58C" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus schirazianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is distinguished by the distinct spreading hairs on the stem. 
<taxonomicName id="847C313DB2AB1538432FFC15D419588D" authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lanuginosus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis id="F398C087CD8BA4E9810EDD97373AAF42" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the pilose ovary and 
<taxonomicName id="E8F054F3A562629A579E82A1047A5813" authorityName="Juz., Bot. Mater. Gerb. Bot. Inst. Komarova Akad. Nauk. S. S. S. R. 12: 219. 1950. (Juzepczuk" authorityYear="1950" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sericocephalus" order="Solanales" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sericocephalus">
<emphasis id="8202CA9EF7CAB83B1A35DF74EF57F9F5" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Convolvulus sericocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the sparse indumentum of the inflorescence so the sepals are easily visible.
</paragraph>
